            "questionText": "A civil engineer is designing a hydroelectric dam. The reservoir has a maximum depth of $!$80 \\text{ m}$!$. The density of water is $!$1000 \\text{ kg/m^3}$!$, and the acceleration due to gravity is $!$9.8 \\text{ m/s^2}$!$. Calculate the hydrostatic pressure in Pascals exerted by the water at the base of the dam wall (assume atmospheric pressure is negligible).",
